# Audio Engine Patterns

## AudioContext initialization

Always start `AudioContext` on a user gesture — never on page load. iOS and Android will block or suspend it otherwise.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — runs on load
const ctx = new AudioContext();

// ✅ GOOD — runs on first user interaction
let ctx: AudioContext | null = null;
function getAudioContext() {
  if (!ctx) ctx = new AudioContext();
  return ctx;
}
```

## Mixing architecture

Each audio layer (scene audio + each texture) gets its own `GainNode` feeding into `AudioContext.destination`:

```
SceneAudioSource → GainNode (scene) ──┐
TextureSource (rain) → GainNode ──────┤→ destination
TextureSource (fire) → GainNode ──────┘
```

All mixing logic lives in `src/lib/audio-engine.ts`. Components only call its public API.

## Session persistence

Gain values are stored in `localStorage` keyed by scene ID via `src/lib/session.ts`. Restore them when returning to a scene:

```ts
// Persist
session.setMix(sceneId, { scene: 0.8, rain: 0.4, fire: 0 });

// Restore
const mix = session.getMix(sceneId);
```

## Mobile limitations

Document known limitations inline when working around them:

```ts
// iOS Safari suspends AudioContext when the page is backgrounded.
// Resume on visibilitychange if state === 'suspended'.
```
